In {{DatanodeInfo#getDatanodeReport}}, we translate {{DatanodeInfo#lastUpdate}} into a date:

{code}
    buffer.append("Last contact: "+new Date(lastUpdate)+"\n");
{code}

This is not going to work if {{lastUpdate}} is a monotonic time.  The easiest way to solve this is to maintain another {{long}} with the wall-clock time, which we set to the current wall-clock time whenever an update occurs.  That way we get the benefits of calculating staleness and deadness based on monotonic time, but also reasonable information in {{getDatanodeReport}}.

{{FSNamesystem#reached}}: The same issue occurs here.

{code}
      if (reached > 0)
        resText += " Threshold was reached " + new Date(reached) + ".";
{code}

{{EditLogTailer#lastLoadTimestamp}}: can we rename this to {{lastLoadTimeMs}}?  It is not a timestamp (those come from the wall clock, generally.)  We could probably get rid of {{EditLogTailer#getLastLoadTimestamp}} since the only use is in {{FSNamesystem#getMillisSinceLastLoadedEdits}}.  All we need is a function which returns the amount of time since the edits were last loaded.
